{
  "texts": [
    "It should be noted that vector spaces already exist in many languages; e.g., the fastText platform provides vector representations of words for 157 languages (Bojanowski et al., 2017; https:// fastt ext. cc/).",
    "Any of these vector spaces can be fed to FMG to create DRM lists easily.",
    "This makes it easy to investigate the impact of semantic relations on false memories across various languages (see Fig. 7A for an example of DRM list with Latin words).",
    "Secondly, FMG can extend the focus of DRM research beyond the impact of semantic relationships between words.",
    "Indeed, it provides a methodological scaffold to explore the role of a wide range of other aspects that could potentially come into play."
  ]
}